	"XSkY0ydA-7" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="green" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Section 112(a) (3) of the Code<BR ALIGN='left'/>recognizes a transfer as tax free only<BR ALIGN='left'/>when 294*294 there is an exchange solely<BR ALIGN='left'/>of stock or securities of &quot;a corporation<BR ALIGN='left'/>a party to a reorganization,&quot; in<BR ALIGN='left'/>pursuance of the plan of reorganization,<BR ALIGN='left'/>for stock or securities in such<BR ALIGN='left'/>corporation or in another corporation a<BR ALIGN='left'/>party to the reorganization. Section<BR ALIGN='left'/>112(b) (4) provides that no gain or loss<BR ALIGN='left'/>shall be recognized if a corporation a<BR ALIGN='left'/>party to the reorganization exchanges<BR ALIGN='left'/>properties, pursuant to a plan of<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganization, solely for stock or<BR ALIGN='left'/>securities in another corporation a<BR ALIGN='left'/>party to the reorganization. But Section<BR ALIGN='left'/>112(c) provides that if property other<BR ALIGN='left'/>than stock or securities be involved in<BR ALIGN='left'/>such a transaction any gain shall be<BR ALIGN='left'/>limited to that the other party<BR ALIGN='left'/>received. Section 112(e) provides that<BR ALIGN='left'/>on such an exchange no loss shall be<BR ALIGN='left'/>recognized.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
